<br>
Spent from 55 to 62+4 AA in pom with my cleric and mage 2 boxing, cleric got 17aa in that time. Took my 56 warrior up to see how 2 boxing would be. a slow weapon would make it easy, but slow. When i went Sssindd did not have a slow weapon or an 8th+ coldain ring so no ds there and our dps was simply too slow to be viable in my opinion; but then, I have never been very patient=). Exp also slows down quite a bit when you hit 62. Basicly, if you are looking for exp comparable to pov/s, don't go to pom. If you are looking for a good time in a new zone, pom is much fun.<br>
<br>
All mobs in the audience/puppets are 55, these are very good, VERY steady exp as you will have basicly unlimited mobs to kill.<br>
<br>
the pom boards mentioned above are very helpful, might also try joining serverwide.pom<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> om  lot of &quot;old time&quot; pomers there who can answer almost any question you can have.<br>
<br>
Yes, CR is very easy. Only 2 or 3 mobs are KoS to all, though some of the halflings are kos by race/class/diety/etc and a few of the puppets will be kos (but they are also rooted, so no biggie)<br>
<br>
In my opinion, yes, it was worth the time spent. Hopefully the revamp won't be long in coming and the zone will be finished for melees. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
