<br>
As a 60 war with ToD, I couldn't really solo for exp- Things just have too many hp. I could do forest/maze with a 57 druid. I could do AiW with a 62 druid and/or 58 cleric. exp was so-so. Card drops were pretty good cept for thrones. Could do Puppets with the 4 of us. Chessboard with cleric and either druid. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17853"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://photo5.matchnet.com/beta/2002/10/15/13205296.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaellewyndemere>Gaelle Wyndemere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/03 8:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of Mischief</span><hr size=1> I did alot of duo'ing (60 warr/60cleric) in PoM prior to PoP release and it was great exp, but once you ding over to 61, you can tell a serious difference in the exp gain. If you have the right gear with ya there you can pretty much do anything (Stomples will be a close fight but if ya got the hps/mana pool you can pull it off). Get an item or wep that snares, a wep that slows, an item that can DS ya (The Blazing arms off Zordak, 8th+ Rings,  or potions) and couple it with mark of retribution, and youre pretty much set.<br>
<br>
PoM is a super fun zone unlike any other in the game, but if your primary goal is exp and youre post 60, Id head to PoV, the exp gain is much better there. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaellewyndemere>Gaelle Wyndemere</A> at: 1/2/03 8:39:44 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=1644.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=1644.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?topicID=1644.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.threadControl?topicID=1644.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1644.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1644.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.e